<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FF84FFF839E60BAB440DBAD3" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF84FFF839E60BAB4211BA67" blockId="10.[136,1452,157,797]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">
<emphasis id="91843240FF84FFF839E60BAB46C7BB98" bold="true" box="[189,489,157,184]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FF84FFF83B5E0BA845BDBB97" authorityName="Heringer &amp; Rizzini" authorityYear="1966" box="[517,659,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="confertum">
<emphasis id="91843240FF84FFF83B5E0BA845BDBB97" box="[517,659,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">S. confertum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF84FFF83A6E0BA8449EBB97" box="[821,944,158,184]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">Goiás state</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF84FFF83ABD0BA843BBBB97" box="[998,1173,158,184]" country="Brazil" name="Distrito Federal" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">Federal District</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry id="DBE7AEC2FF84FFF83DFF0BA843C0BB96" box="[1188,1262,158,185]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">Brazil</collectingCountry>
), in cerrado 
<emphasis id="91843240FF84FFF83C230BA94282BB97" box="[1400,1452,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">s.str.</emphasis>
or campo cerrado, usually on rocky and / or sandy soil. The area where the 
<typeStatus id="7C4B50F0FF84FFF83AA70BF44370BBF3" box="[1020,1118,194,220]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected in the 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF84FFF83C0C0BF447F1BA2F" country="Brazil" name="Distrito Federal" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">Federal District</collectingRegion>
, Granja do Torto, is currently a residential district of Brasília, with few areas still unoccupied. Other collections are referred to the 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF84FFF838010A3C4522BA0B" box="[346,524,266,292]" country="Brazil" name="Distrito Federal" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">Federal District</collectingRegion>
, such as the Santa Maria dam, in a legally protected area (Brasilia National Park). No natural populations of this species were found on recent visits to the species´s known distribution range.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF84FFF839E60A64440DBAD3" blockId="10.[136,1452,157,797]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">
The label of the specimen 
<emphasis id="91843240FF84FFF838860A6545EFBA43" box="[477,705,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">E.P. Heringer 14748</emphasis>
(UB) reads “cultivated in Brasilia from seeds from the municipality of Cristalina, 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF84FFF838450A4046B0BABF" box="[286,414,374,400]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">Goiás state</collectingRegion>
”. However, duplicates of this collection at HB and MO showed mixed samples of 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FF84FFF83C440A404282BABF" authorityName="Heringer &amp; Rizzini" authorityYear="1966" box="[1311,1452,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="confertum">
<emphasis id="91843240FF84FFF83C440A404282BABF" box="[1311,1452,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">S. confertum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FF84FFF839ED0AAC4667BA9B" authorityName="Heringer (Rizzini &amp; Mattos Filho" authorityYear="1968" box="[182,329,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cristalinae">
<emphasis id="91843240FF84FFF839ED0AAC4667BA9B" box="[182,329,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">S. cristalinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and certainly the label information corresponds to 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FF84FFF83AD10AAC4333BA9B" authorityName="Heringer (Rizzini &amp; Mattos Filho" authorityYear="1968" box="[906,1053,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cristalinae">
<emphasis id="91843240FF84FFF83AD10AAC4333BA9B" box="[906,1053,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">S. cristalinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is endemic to Cristalina (see comments of this species). Recent expeditions to Cristalina failed to find any population of 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FF84FFF83DC90A88420FBAF7" authorityName="Heringer &amp; Rizzini" authorityYear="1966" box="[1170,1313,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="confertum">
<emphasis id="91843240FF84FFF83DC90A88420FBAF7" box="[1170,1313,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">S. confertum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, reinforcing the distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FF84FFF838030AD446C8BAD3" authorityName="Heringer &amp; Rizzini" authorityYear="1966" box="[344,486,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="confertum">
<emphasis id="91843240FF84FFF838030AD446C8BAD3" box="[344,486,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">S. confertum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the sites indicated above.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FF84FFF839E60933467DB947" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF84FFF839E60933467DB947" blockId="10.[136,1452,157,797]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">
<emphasis id="91843240FF84FFF839E609334649B930" bold="true" box="[189,359,517,543]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">Conservation:</emphasis>
—Endangered (EN B1ab(i,ii,iii)+2ab(i,ii,iii) [AOO= 
<quantity id="640843B7FF84FFF83AF60930430BB90F" box="[941,1061,518,544]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" unit="km" value="16.0">16.000 km</quantity>
<superScript id="5485431AFF84FFF83D7E09304303B93B" attach="left" box="[1061,1069,518,532]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">2</superScript>
, EOO = 
<quantity id="640843B7FF84FFF83DD609304208B90F" box="[1165,1318,518,544]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.134284" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" unit="km" value="1134.284">1,134.284 km</quantity>
<superScript id="5485431AFF84FFF83C7E09304203B93B" attach="left" box="[1317,1325,518,532]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">2</superScript>
]. Although natural populations of 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FF84FFF838D1091C4534B96B" authorityName="Heringer &amp; Rizzini" authorityYear="1966" box="[394,538,554,580]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="confertum">
<emphasis id="91843240FF84FFF838D1091C4534B96B" box="[394,538,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">S. confertum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are found within a legally protected area, this species occurs in a restricted and threatened region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FF84FFF839E6094446DDB99F" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" type="description">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF84FFF839E6094446DDB99F" blockId="10.[136,1452,157,797]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">
<emphasis id="91843240FF84FFF839E60944466DB9A3" bold="true" box="[189,323,626,652]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">Phenology:</emphasis>
—Flowering specimens were collected in June and from September to November, fruiting specimens were collected in May and June.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
